    "body": "I cannot help with any detailed code analysis, but I can confirm the following\r\n(based on 2 running instances of erigon, ethereum mainnet on separate servers each with their own config file and data directory):\r\n\r\n- v2.48.1 and below have been running on my servers fine for months, no memory problems\r\n- v2.49 and higher eat up all available system memory within around 1 day, then the process gets killed by the OS\r\n- after rolling back to v2.48.1 the problem disappears (tested this independently and separately on both servers)\r\n- nothing else was changed when rolling back (database, config file, all the same - I simply stopped the process running v.2.49.x, then started v.2.28.1 and the memory leak problem disappears\r\n\r\nI am not able to pinpoint the issue in the code, but there is without a doubt a memory leak problem that was introduced in 2.49",
