    "body": "https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/pull/8305 has a fix for one of the causes of this issue.  I won't close this yet as I'm not sure its the only one.\r\n\r\nI think whenever we get delays in processing headers and we're a significant distance from the head of the chain (>1M Blocks) we will see this issue.\r\n\r\nIts not clear at the moment if we should fix this to provide a smaller max overall memory footprint (i.e. make the header list size memory dependent) or leave it as is.  ",
