    "body": "I can also confirm this issue started happening for us when we upgraded from `2.43.1` to `2.49.3`, now our nodes OOM every 6d or so.  Furthermore we are seeing this issue across all three Ethereum L1 networks (mainnet, Sepolia, goerli) and it looks like #8305 is specific to Polygon so I doubt the issue is really resolved.\r\n\r\nA couple of interesting data points:\r\n\r\n- One of our nodes was reporting using roughly 70GB of memory for `erigon`, yet Go's `pprof` tool only reported around 5GB in use.\r\n\r\nThis same node stopped importing new blocks with this error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nOct 21 07:58:13 ip-10-0-65-144 erigon[10575]: [INFO] [10-21|07:58:13.293] head updated                             hash=0x94ed128805345b3244b32a21b019862c13af24e96df41fd06ee1fa4c123ce065 number=18397343\r\nOct 21 07:58:24 ip-10-0-65-144 erigon[10575]: [INFO] [10-21|07:58:24.109] [NewPayload] Handling new payload        height=18397344 hash=0x2a9873afd92f30005a96f4a904d36278c01464ce9fc5a63df8b4ebb884988153\r\nOct 21 07:58:32 ip-10-0-65-144 erigon[10575]: [EROR] [10-21|07:58:32.240] RPC method engine_newPayloadV2 crashed: fail to open mdbx: mdbx_env_open: cannot allocate memory, label: inMem, trace: [kv_mdbx.go:263 kv_mdbx.go:396 memory_mutation.go:47 fork_validator.go:150 ethereum_execution.go:181 execution_client.go:59 chain_reader.go:288 engine_server.go:721 engine_server.go:234 engine_server.go:573 value.go:586 value.go:370 service.go:224 handler.go:494 handler.go:444 handler.go:392 handler.go:223 handler.go:316 asm_amd64.s:1598]\r\nOct 21 07:58:32 ip-10-0-65-144 erigon[10575]: [service.go:219 panic.go:884 kv_mdbx.go:398 memory_mutation.go:47 fork_validator.go:150 ethereum_execution.go:181 execution_client.go:59 chain_reader.go:288 engine_server.go:721 engine_server.go:234 engine_server.go:573 value.go:586 value.go:370 service.go:224 handler.go:494 handler.go:444 handler.go:392 handler.go:223 handler.go:316 asm_amd64.s:1598]\r\nOct 21 07:58:32 ip-10-0-65-144 erigon[10575]: [WARN] [10-21|07:58:32.240] Served                                   conn=127.0.0.1:52952 method=engine_newPayloadV2 reqid=201088 t=8.133393463s err=\"method handler crashed\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis leads me to believe that the issue is in erigon's use of MBDX, since Go is not seeing the memory from pprof its most likely a leak in the buffers managed by the MBDX C/C++ code.",
